    {
      "text": "Identify the instrument:",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Bohler braun splint"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Thomas splint"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Volkmann splint"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Cramer wire"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Bohler Braun Splint:</strong></p>\n\n<h4><strong>Structure & Mechanism:</strong></h4>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><strong>Heavy <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"84433cae211692777192a484f539bc\">metallic</span> frame with four pulleys for traction:</strong>\n\n\t<ol>\n\t\t<li>Prevents foot drop.</li>\n\t\t<li>Applies <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"66d1f5d3461692777200af5741a710\">traction</span> in the line of the femur.</li>\n\t\t<li>Traction in the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"043a86fa0016927771998a67e65e6a\">supracondylar</span> area of the femur.</li>\n\t\t<li>Traction in the line of the leg.</li>\n\t</ol>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4><strong>Indications:</strong></h4>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Comminuted trochanteric fractures of the femur.</li>\n\t<li>Fracture <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"665018e7801692777198b82c6c9db8\">shaft</span> of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"512283ec9816927772024c89478b7d\">femur</span> & <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"043a86fa0016927771998a67e65e6a\">supracondylar</span> fractures.</li>\n\t<li>Occasionally used for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f2a519f38316927772004fe7c606af\">tibial</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b3f5142f22169277720272cecbf67c\">fibular</span> fractures.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4><strong>Precaution:</strong></h4>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Support should be given at the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e3727bc4841692777203d62242b6e6\">fracture</span> site, not the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9d86b5d3351692777190224c62427b\">knee joint</span> to prevent <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1aec9f83db16927771815b94ad8e86\">angulation</span> (especially in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"043a86fa0016927771998a67e65e6a\">supracondylar</span> fractures).</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4><strong>Problems:</strong></h4>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li>Difficult <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6f686e0c91169277719346f95361c8\">nursing</span> care.</li>\n\t<li>Heavy and cumbersome.</li>\n\t<li>Risk of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ece1d5637c169277719789b25ff95b\">recumbent</span> complications (bedsores, pneumonia, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b9356afdba16927771979d068c6587\">renal</span> calculi).</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Thomas <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7f606f911b1692777199eb69ab67c5\">splint</span> (Option B):</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Used primarily for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ab8a987431169277720229e09c01d7\">femoral</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"665018e7801692777198b82c6c9db8\">shaft</span> fractures.</li>\n\t<li>Features a ring at the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bdbac654081692777196f9aab116f0\">proximal</span> end to support the thigh.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"\" data-source=\"\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"503\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/mGhcVlckSObxqQzakuBt1741059431.png\" width=\"415\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>Volkmann <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7f606f911b1692777199eb69ab67c5\">splint</span> (Option C):</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Used for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"258a5bb5841692777203cfb8e31f55\">forearm</span> fractures and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3024d9916e16927771896f5b7159b6\">immobilization</span> of the wrist/elbow.</li>\n\t<li>Prevents contractures (e.g., Volkmann’s ischemic contracture). </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"\" data-source=\"\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"313\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/Q9DnAAi5h5lJsf4Xl2RM1741059475.png\" width=\"312\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>Cramer wire (Option D): </strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>A <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f17e2af4831692777191f10a806f74\">malleable</span> metal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7f606f911b1692777199eb69ab67c5\">splint</span> used for temporary <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3024d9916e16927771896f5b7159b6\">immobilization</span> of fractures.</li>\n\t<li>Shaped according to limb contours.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"\" data-source=\"\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"475\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/sgL0lzIaDQy9ZSZjuowe1741059546.png\" width=\"671\" /></p>\n\n<p> </p>",
